<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Malbak reports last pre-unbundling earnings.</title>
<headline>Malbak reports last pre-unbundling earnings.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year ended February 28</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>Shr, (cts)</p>
<p>    - pre-exceps	    80.3	  vs 80.8</p>
<p>    - post exceps	   63.4	  vs 80.5</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 none	  vs 18.0</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   271.0	 vs 271.0</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   510.0	 vs 496.0</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   74.0	  vs 84.0</p>
<p>    Turnover		  8,668.0     vs 8,513.0</p>
<p>Full name: Malbak Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - Directors said that due to the radical changes which have taken place in Malbak recently -- most units were sold off as the group unbundled -- results were not comparable with a year ago.</p>
<p>During the six month period Malbak sold its interestsin Tedelex, Eagle Freight, Stalcor and Defy. As Malbak Motor Holdings and Osborn MMD were sold off after the period, their earnings are included in the income statement, directors said.</p>
<p>As Malbak shareholders would be receiving dividends from most of the underlying companies whose shares have distributed in the unbundling, Malbak itself had not declared an interim dividend.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
